The paper deals with managing software complexity and solving optimization problems related to package-based systems, which are typical concerns in software engineering (cs.SE). The use of Boolean satisfiability (SAT) is a common technique in programming languages and compilers (cs.PL), and the problem of managing dependencies and conflicts can also be seen as a data structure or algorithmic problem (cs.DS). The evaluation of the tools involves optimization criteria, which is a topic in machine learning and optimization (cs.LG), and the use of SAT solvers can also be seen as an application of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
